      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__regulator__parent__interface_1gaa65d0a8d792256818a2ba06ad67a4f02" prot="public" static="yes" const="no" explicit="no" inline="yes" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>static int regulator_parent_ship_mode</definition>
        <argsstring>(const struct device *dev)</argsstring>
        <name>regulator_parent_ship_mode</name>
        <param>
          <type>const struct <ref refid="structdevice" kindref="compound">device</ref> *</type>
          <declname>dev</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Enter ship mode. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Some PMICs feature a ship mode, which allows the system to save power. Exit from low power is normally by pin transition.</para>
<para>This API can be used when ship mode needs to be entered.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dev</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Parent regulator device instance.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>0</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If successful. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-ENOSYS</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If function is not implemented. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-errno</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>In case of any other error. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
